summary: DoctorThasmin’s Doctor Who Questions Favourite Doctor: 13 and 10. For similar reasons, 10 was my favourite Doctor until 13...
body:
DoctorThasmin’s Doctor Who Questions

  1. Favourite Doctor: 13 and 10. For similar reasons, 10 was my favourite Doctor until 13 because he was the Doctor that set my imagination on fire as a child. 13 is my favourite now because she’s reignited my joy for a character and a story that still brings me so much joy as an adult. Plus I love a silly chatty (accented) Doctor.
  2. Favourite Doctor Who Companion: Donna Noble, today, tomorrow, forever. (If Grace had lived, she could have been a very close second!)
  3. Favourite Doctor Who Episode: “Rise of the Cybermen” S2 E5. and “Journey’s End” S4 E13.
  4. Favourite Doctor Who Villain: Davros, I love the Daleks as the arch nemesis of the Doctor. 
  5. Best Character Chemistry in Doctor Who: 13  and Yaz for romantic chemistry and 10 and Donna for platonic chemistry. 
  6. Funniest Doctor: 12, but I was a massive fan of Peter Capaldi before Doctor Who and I just adore his witty humour which he brought to his characterisation. Plus grumpy granddads make me laugh read: I love Graham too. 
  7. Saddest Doctor: I’ve heard arguments for 9 but to be honest, I say 10 every time. He had so much to lose, and he wasn’t ready to go. Plus he left knowing Rose got their happy ending without him. I mean come on. 
  8. Best Series of Doctor Who: My favourite is probably Series 3, it had some of the best stories and most consistent pace. 
  9. Best Irregular Character: Mickey Smith, no contest. 
  10. Doctor Who OTP: I’m of the belief that every Doctor has their own love story that doesn’t necessarily shift from Doctor to Doctor, so I do ship 10xRose, 11xRiver, 12xClara or River, and yes 13xYaz. 
  11. One thing you’d change: Stripping Donna of her memories was an insult to the character and her sacrifices. But, she was also beloved by the fan base so I can’t see how else, besides killing her, they could have moved on from her. 
  12. Best Doctor Who Writer: Russell T Davies was very traditional Doctor Who and I love a lot of his other work too. But I have to say Chibnall has impressed me in his bravery, I wasn’t keen on the stand alone episode idea, but it really worked for me in Season 11. For individual episode, it’s Malorie Blackman, Rosa knocked me sideways - just incredible. 
  13. One thing you’d like to see in the future series: I’d like to see 13 meet a past companion or a past self. My current vote is for Martha or Jack, as they both could be easily written in, and for self I’d say maybe 11 to be honest, he’s the only one who wouldn’t make a big deal out of it I think :)
